[SN]TITLE[SN]
Welsh Architecture Awards 2017: Four buildings shortlisted

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Four buildings have been shortlisted for the Welsh Architecture Awards 2017.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Royal Society of Architects announced One Central Square in Cardiff, Rhyl High School in Denbighshire, and the Silver House in Gower, were in the running.
The Chickenshed, Monmouthshire, completes the shortlist.
All the buildings will be visited by a regional jury before the winner is announced at an award ceremony at Cardiff and Vale College on 30 May.
The winners will be in the running for the UK-wide 2017 Royal Institute of British Architects (RIBA) Stirling Prize for the best building of the year.
